  "prompt": "Did any of Melania Trump's family come to her wedding? Did anyone \"give her away?\" And who paid for her wedding gown?",
  "response": "Melania Trump\u2019s wedding to Donald Trump on January 22, 2005, took place at the Episcopal St. Andrew's Cathedral in Palm Beach, Florida. While specific details about her family\u2019s attendance at the wedding are limited, it has been reported that her parents, Viktor and Amalija Knavs, attended the ceremony. \n\nAs for the question of who \"gave her away,\" it was actually Donald Trump who walked Melania down the aisle, as her father was not able to take on that role. \n\nRegarding who paid for her wedding gown, it is widely believed that Donald Trump himself covered the costs, as he did for many aspects of the wedding. Melania's wedding dress was designed by John Galliano for Christian Dior, and it has been noted for its elegance and luxury.",
